### BUG12: Ask to register incident after creating trap
In onContainerClick, the doAction for creating a new trap has an onClose callback. Modify it to ask the user if they want to register an incident:

Find the onClose callback in onContainerClick (where it opens pest.trap form). Change it to:

onClose: async () => {
    await this.loadData();
    // Ask if user wants to register an incident for the new trap
    const registerIncident = window.confirm('Trampa creada. Desea registrar una incidencia?');
    if (registerIncident) {
        // Find the most recently created trap (last in the list)
        const traps = this.state.data.traps;
        if (traps && traps.length > 0) {
            const newestTrap = traps[traps.length - 1];
            await this.onRegisterIncident(newestTrap);
        }
    }
}

### BUG13: Incident form doesn't preload sede and blueprint
Check the onRegisterIncident method. It should pass default_sede_id and default_blueprint_id in the context. Verify:

async onRegisterIncident(trap) {
    await this.action.doAction({
        type: 'ir.actions.act_window',
        res_model: 'pest.incident',
        views: [[false, 'form']],
        target: 'new',
        context: {
            default_trap_id: trap.id,
            default_blueprint_id: this.props.record.resId,
            default_sede_id: trap.sede_id || (this.state.data && this.state.data.sede_id) || false,
        },
    }, {
        onClose: () => this.loadData(),
    });
    this.state.selectedTrapId = null;
}

Make sure default_sede_id is always passed. The sede_id should come from trap.sede_id (if available) or from this.state.data.sede_id (which was added in a previous task).

